    <fr:title text="Chain Rule of Mutual Info">Chain Rule of Mutual Info</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
    We have that
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
      \begin {align*}
        I(X, Y; Z) = I(X; Z) + I(Y; Z | X)
      \end {align*}
    ]]></fr:tex></html:p>
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    By definition,
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
        \begin {align*}
          I(X, Y; Z) &= H(X,Y) + H(Z) - H(X, Y, Z) \\
          &= H(X) + H(Y | X) + H(Z) - H(X, Z) - H(Y | X, Z) \\
          &= H(X) + H(Y | X) + H(Z) - H(X, Z) - H(Y | X, Z) \\
          &= I(X; Z) + H(Y | X) - (H(Y, Z | X) - H(Z | X)) \\
          &= I(X; Z) + I(Y; Z | X)
        \end {align*}
    ]]></fr:tex>
    as desired
  </fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 

